Package cellery

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Cell
    Cells are objects with two states: dead or alive.
    CellArray1D
    CellArray1D is a 1-d array of Cell objects which can kill or resurrect Cells and retrieve neighborhoods about individual Cells.
    CellArray2D
    A CellArray is a 2-d array of Cell objects which can kill and revive Cells and retrieve neighborhoods about individual cells.
    CellArrayCylinder
    CellArray2D embedded in a Cylindrical Space
    CellArrayMobius
    CellArray2D on a Moebius Strip
    CellerySeeds
    Provides methods that can provide initial conditions for Cellular Automata rules.
    CellularAutomata
    CellularAutomata is an object that can evolve Cells contained within a CellArray2D or CellArray1D.
    CellularAutomata1D
    CellularAutomata1D is a 1 dimensional extension CellularAutomata
    CellularAutomata2D
    CellularAutomata2D is a 2 dimensional extension of CellularAutomata
    DayAndNight
    CellularAutomata2D endowed with the Day & Night Rules.
    Life
    CellularAutomata2D endowed with the Game of Life rules
    Sierpenski
    Generates a Sierpenski triangle using Cellular Automata rules
    TessellationAutomata2
    CellularAutomata2D endowed with Tessellation rules of type 2.
    TessellationAutomata4A
    CellularAutomata2D endowed with Tessellation rules of type 4A.
    TessellationAutomata4B
    CellularAutomata2D endowed with Tessellation rules of type 4A.
